A man has been arrested on suspicion of killing an elderly dog walker following an alleged row over their pets, police said today.

Peter Morley, 74, was walking his small brown terrier dog Bella when it is believed she was attacked by two other Staffordshire bull terriers in Bexhill-on-Sea, East Sussex.

Mr Morley suffered a head injury during a row with the owner of the two dogs on Turkey Road in the town on July 20 and was taken to hospital but died ten days later.

